  <front>
    <title>DHCP Auto-configure Option (Option code 116) Deprecated</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-droms-rfc2563-deprecate-00"/>
    <author initials="R." surname="Droms" fullname="Ralph Droms">
      <organization>Cisco Systems</organization>
    </author>
    <date day="14" month="May" year="2002"></date>
    <abstract>
      <t>RFC2563 defines the DHCP Auto-configure option, which controls
whether a DHCP client uses address auto-configuration.  Because of
the potential threat of a denial of service attack, the use of
RFC2563 is deprecated.

	 </t>
    </abstract>
  </front>
